Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 14:58:02 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Cache behaviors in scan order to avoid iterator allocation

Two edge cases currently not used by vanilla behavior implementation differ from vanilla as a trade-off:

1. If a behavior stops another lower-priority behavior in the same activity, the stopped behavior will no longer be ticked.
   Vanilla getRunningBehaviors returns a snapshot, so it may still be ticked in that cycle.
2. If a behavior changes the activity when starting, lower-priority behaviors in the same activity will no longer start.
   Vanilla activity check is done only once per activity.

Vanilla behavior priority semantics should be preserved.

